03:51.540 --> 03:55.240
<i>Could y'all give me a hand here
And help me fix this mess?</i>

03:55.390 --> 03:57.820
<i>My destiny is not pretty</i>

03:58.230 --> 04:01.680
<i>But it's what
My cutie mark is tellin' me</i>

04:04.300 --> 04:08.650
<i>I'm in love with weather patterns
But the others have concerns</i>

04:08.800 --> 04:13.100
<i>For I just gave them frostbite
Over-top of their sunburns</i>

04:13.870 --> 04:17.660
<i>I have to keep on trying
For everyone can see</i>

04:17.800 --> 04:19.950
<i>It's got to be</i>

04:19.950 --> 04:22.050
<i>My destiny</i>

04:22.050 --> 04:24.300
<i>And it's what my cutie mark</i>

04:24.300 --> 04:26.070
<i>It's what my cutie mark</i>

04:26.070 --> 04:30.800
<i>Yes, it's what
My cutie mark is telling me!</i>

04:34.100 --> 04:36.700
This is bad.
This is very, very bad!

04:36.850 --> 04:39.360
What's going on?
Why is this happening?!

04:39.510 --> 04:42.270
Last night when you were taking
one of your seven-hour bubble baths,

04:42.420 --> 04:45.120
<i>I got a special delivery
from the princess.</i>

04:48.840 --> 04:50.370
Dear Twilight Sparkle,

04:50.520 --> 04:52.720
The spell contained
on the last page of this book

04:52.840 --> 04:56.470
is Star Swirl the Bearded's
secret unfinished masterpiece.

04:58.060 --> 05:01.550
He was never able to get it right,
and thus abandoned it.

05:01.700 --> 05:05.420
I believe you are the only pony
who can understand and rewrite it.

05:05.540 --> 05:07.340
Princess Celestia.

05:07.770 --> 05:10.410
From one to another,
another to one.

05:10.560 --> 05:13.850
A mark of one's destiny
singled out alone, fulfilled.

05:16.500 --> 05:20.100
That doesn't make any sense.
It doesn't even rhyme!

05:20.680 --> 05:23.440
<i>I cast the spell
so I could find out what it was.</i>

05:23.560 --> 05:25.570
<i>But nothing seemed to happen.</i>

05:26.280 --> 05:28.440
But now I know something did happen.

05:28.560 --> 05:31.020
The spell has changed
the Elements of Harmony!

05:31.140 --> 05:34.040
That must be why
their cutie marks are all wrong!

05:34.160 --> 05:36.430
So just cast a counter-spell
to switch them back!

05:36.980 --> 05:39.110
There is no counter-spell!

05:39.230 --> 05:42.340
What about that memory spell you used
to fix everypony when Discord was here?

05:42.460 --> 05:44.110
It's not their memories, Spike.

05:44.230 --> 05:46.400
It's their true selves
that have been altered!

05:46.590 --> 05:50.080
- Zecora's cure for the Cutie Pox?
- That won't work either...

05:51.260 --> 05:53.650
Well, maybe it won't be so bad.

05:53.770 --> 05:56.010
Maybe our friends will grow
to like their new lives?

05:56.130 --> 05:59.300
No Spike. They're not
who they are meant to be anymore.

05:59.420 --> 06:01.710
Their destinies are now changed.

06:01.830 --> 06:03.710
And it's all my fault...

06:12.170 --> 06:15.870
<i>I have to find a way</i>

06:16.100 --> 06:19.460
<i>To make this all okay</i>

06:20.120 --> 06:24.170
<i>I can't believe this small mistake</i>

06:24.320 --> 06:27.380
<i>Could've caused so much heartache</i>

06:27.530 --> 06:31.500
<i>Oh why</i>

06:31.650 --> 06:35.510
<i>Oh why</i>

06:35.660 --> 06:39.870
<i>Losing promise</i>

06:39.990 --> 06:43.270
<i>I don't know what to do</i>

06:43.850 --> 06:47.660
<i>Seeking answers</i>

06:47.790 --> 06:54.400
<i>I fear I won't get through to you</i>

06:55.490 --> 06:59.410
<i>Oh why</i>

06:59.660 --> 07:02.790
<i>Oh why</i>

07:05.640 --> 07:10.360
Oh, Spike, what have I done?

07:13.420 --> 07:17.320
Aw, come on, Twilight,
you'll figure out a way to fix this.

07:17.440 --> 07:19.610
These are your friends.

07:22.310 --> 07:23.620
You're right, Spike.

07:26.050 --> 07:28.790
And they mean more to me
than anything.

07:29.430 --> 07:31.710
My friends...

07:32.980 --> 07:35.420
Twilight?
Are you alright?

07:37.280 --> 07:39.430
I've got it! I know what to do!

07:39.550 --> 07:40.340
You do?

07:40.530 --> 07:43.410
I may not be able
to remind them of who they are,

07:43.530 --> 07:45.750
but I can show them
what they mean to each other.

07:45.870 --> 07:48.280
They'll find the part of themselves
that's been lost so they can

07:48.280 --> 07:50.750
help the friend
they care about so much!

07:50.870 --> 07:52.620
Come on, Spike!

07:55.930 --> 07:57.260
Fluttershy, wait!

07:59.360 --> 08:02.740
- Oh... Hey, Twilight...
- Where are you going?

08:02.860 --> 08:04.700
I'm moving back to Cloudsdale.

08:04.820 --> 08:08.450
I don't know what's wrong,
but I can't seem to make anypony laugh.

08:11.800 --> 08:13.110
Before you go,

08:13.230 --> 08:16.190
I was wondering if you might
be willing to help Rainbow Dash.

08:16.310 --> 08:18.670
She's really struggling
with her animals.

08:18.790 --> 08:23.130
But I don't really know
anything about animals...

08:23.250 --> 08:25.630
But you do know something
about Rainbow Dash.

08:26.940 --> 08:30.230
I know
that she's a true friend,

08:30.350 --> 08:33.630
and I'll do
anything I can to help her!

08:37.730 --> 08:38.990
Rainbow Dash!

08:39.110 --> 08:42.580
I'm in here! Help!
I'm trapped!

08:42.700 --> 08:46.200
Hurry, Twilight! Can't you do
some sort of spell to get her out?

08:46.320 --> 08:47.230
No.

08:47.350 --> 08:49.880
Fluttershy,
you're the only one who can help!

08:50.000 --> 08:52.490
Rainbow Dash needs you!

08:55.520 --> 08:57.610
Um... Hello?

08:57.730 --> 09:00.530
Little... woodland creatures?

09:03.020 --> 09:05.630
I know that
you're all very upset,

09:05.750 --> 09:07.970
and feel like giving
Rainbow Dash a hard time,

09:08.090 --> 09:11.310
but we'd all really appreciate it
if you'd calm down and, um,

09:11.430 --> 09:13.490
maybe rest for a bit?

09:15.880 --> 09:17.370
Oh! Uh... look!

09:17.490 --> 09:21.240
Here's some nice, juicy leaves
for you to munch on.

09:21.360 --> 09:24.470
And some crunchy,
munchy acorns too.

09:24.800 --> 09:28.830
Uh, wouldn't you like to take a break
and have a little snack?

09:31.330 --> 09:36.040
Aw, look at that. I guess you were
all just cranky because you were hungry.

09:37.570 --> 09:41.250
Oh, you are very welcome,
little friends.

09:43.230 --> 09:46.210
Goodness, it's like
I can understand them!

09:46.330 --> 09:48.810
I... I feel strange, like...

09:48.930 --> 09:52.830
like this is what I'm meant to do,
like this is who I am!

09:52.950 --> 09:54.670
My destiny!

10:02.270 --> 10:03.980
Wha... what happened?

10:04.100 --> 10:06.500
Fluttershy, look!
Your cutie mark!

10:09.160 --> 10:11.210
It worked!
It worked!

10:11.330 --> 10:13.670
Oh, I'm so happy
you're back to normal!

10:14.030 --> 10:15.400
Now, we need your help!

10:16.180 --> 10:20.420
<i>A true, true friend
Helps a friend in need</i>

10:20.540 --> 10:24.450
<i>A friend will be there
To help them see</i>

10:24.570 --> 10:27.910
